value.value: 全身血管抵抗の上昇
increase in the normal force opposing blood flow in the peripheral blood vessels
全身血管抵抗の低下
reduction in the normal force opposing blood flow in the peripheral blood vessels
肺嚢
presence of one or more abnormal membranous or fluid-filled sacs in the lung
肺サイズの異常
anomaly in the size of the lung compared to controls
肺の肥大化
increased size of the lung compared to controls
血管治癒の異常
anomaly in the repair process of damaged blood vessels after injury
精巣の生理異常
any functional anomaly of the male reproductive glands
内リンパの異常

any alteration in the normal production (volume) or ionic homeostasis of the fluid contained within the membranous labyrinth of the inner ear; unlike perilymph, endolymph resembles intracellular fluid in composition and has a high concentration of potassium ion and a low concentration of sodium ion
内リンパ産生の異常
increased synthesis of the fluid that is normally contained within the membranous labyrinth of the inner ear
内リンパ産生の減少
reduced synthesis of the fluid that is normally contained within the membranous labyrinth of the inner ear
外リンパの異常

change in the normal production (volume) or ionic homeostasis of the fluid contained within the osseous labyrinth, surrounding and protecting the membranous labyrinth; perilymph resembles extracellular fluid in composition, has a high concentration of sodium ion and a low concentration of potassium ion and, through the perilymphatic duct, is in continuity with cerebrospinal fluid
エネルギー消費の増加
increase in the number of calories used per unit time or decrease in weight gain for a given amount of food eaten
エネルギー消費の減少
decrease in the number of calories used per unit time or increase in weight gain for a given amount of food eaten
アディポネクチン値異常
abnormal level of a protein hormone that regulates glucose homeostasis and metabolism of lipids; it is normally produced by adipose tissue
アディポネクチン値上昇
greater level of a protein hormone that regulates glucose homeostasis and metabolism of lipids; it is normally produced by adipose tissue
アディポネクチン値低下
reduced concentration of a protein hormone that regulates glucose homeostasis and metabolism of lipids; it is normally produced by adipose tissue
子宮委縮

acquired diminution of the size of the uterus associated with wasting as from death and reabsorption of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes
膣委縮

acquired diminution of the size of the vagina associated with wasting as from death and reabsorption of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes
子宮内膜の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the glandular mucous membrane lining of the uterine cavity that is hormonally responsive during the estrous/menstrual cycle and during pregnancy
耳硬化症

formation of spongy bone in the bony labyrinth of the ear, especially adjacent to the footplate of the stapes; it may cause bony ankylosis of the stapes, resulting in conductive hearing loss; cochlear otosclerosis results in sensorineural hearing loss
子宮出血
presence of bleeding in the uterus; often in response to failed pregnancy
側頭鱗骨の欠如
absence of the anterosuperior portion of the temporal bone that is thin, scale-like, and translucent and forms part of the lateral wall of the cranial vault
頬骨弓の欠如

absence of the bony arch that extends along the side or front of the skull beneath the eye socket and is formed by the temporal process of the zygomatic bone and the zygomatic process of the temporal bone
雄性生殖細胞数の減少
reduced numbers of male germ cells whether they are undifferentiated or fully differentiated
子宮サイズの異常
anomaly in the size of the female organ of gestation
子宮重量の異常
anomaly in the weight of the female organ of gestation
子宮重量の増加
increase in the weight of the female organ of gestation
子宮重量の減少
reduction in the weight of the female organ of gestation
子宮の肥大化
increased size of the female muscular organ of gestation
精嚢腺サイズの異常
anomaly in the size of one or both of the two folded, sac shaped, glands that is a diverticulum of the ductus deferens
精嚢腺重量の異常
anomaly in the weight of one or both of the two folded, sac shaped, glands that is a diverticulum of the ductus deferens
精嚢腺重量の増加
increase in the weight of one or both of the two folded, sac shaped, glands that is a diverticulum of the ductus deferens
精嚢腺重量の減少
reduction in the weight of one or both of the two folded, sac shaped, glands that is a diverticulum of the ductus deferens
下顎鉤状突起の欠如

absence of the round bump of bone and constricted neck portion that arises from the upper surface of the mandibular ramus (perpendicular portion) and articulates with the articular disk of the temporomandibular joint
下顎鉤状突起の欠如
absence of the thin, flattened, triangular eminence that arises from the upper surface of the mandibular ramus (perpendicular portion)
下顎角の欠如
absence of the portion of the mandible where the body of the mandible (horizontal portion) and the rami (perpendicular portions) meet; these normally unite nearly at right angles
後鰓体の欠如

absence of the outpocketing of the caudal-most branchial pouch of the embryo (interpreted as a fifth pouch in human or as the ventral component of the fourth pouch in mouse) that fuses with the thyroid diverticulum, ultimately giving rise to calcitonin-producing parafollicular cells (aka C-cells) which function in calcium homeostasis; in most mammals, these parafollicular cells fully disperse with the endodermally derived follicular cells of the thyroid by birth
第2鰓弓（舌骨弓）軟骨の異常

any structural anomaly of the cartilage found in the mesenchyme of the second pharyngeal arch in the embryo from which develop the stapes, styloid process, lesser horn and upper part of the body of the hyoid bone; its proximal end gives rise to the stylohyoid ligament
第2鰓弓（舌骨弓）軟骨の欠如

absence of the cartilage normally found in the mesenchyme of the second branchial arch in the embryo, from which develop the stapes, the styloid processes, the stylohyoid ligaments, and the lesser cornua of the hyoid bone
T細胞選択の異常
any anomaly in the process through which T cells that express T cell receptors that are restricted by self MHC protein complexes and tolerant to self antigens are selected for further maturation
負のT細胞選択の異常
any anomaly in the process of elimination of immature T cells which react strongly with self-antigens
正のT細胞選択の異常
any anomaly in the process of sparing immature T cells which react with self-MHC protein complexes with low affinity levels from apoptotic death
胎盤重の増加
increase in the weight of the organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother
胎盤重の減少
reduction in the weight of the organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother
総脚形態の異常
any structural anomaly in the united, nonampullary ends of the superior and posterior semicircular ducts of the inner ear
総脚の欠損
absence of the united, nonampullary ends of the superior and posterior semicircular ducts in the inner ear
行動異常
any anomaly in the actions, reactions, or performance of an organism in response to external or internal stimuli compared to controls

anomaly in the size of the elongated structure connected to the posterior surface of the testis that transports, stores, and matures spermatozoa between testis and vas deferens
